metadata.name: you can't consume me
metadata.description:
This artwork serves as a reminder to be unapologetically yourself.  
With the oil paint covering the body of the subject, this signifies all the fake misinformation in the world, trying to corrupt and change you. However the mind is blocked off, you can't consume all of me, my mind is strong, and I will fight for what I believe in. Shapes ground me, they have been here since the beginning of time, and they will continue to hold ties to the real world.  
Photo based mixed media work.
